Title of Honorary Citizen of Mongolia to Kim Jong Il 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il was awarded the title of the honorary citizen of Darhan Ol Province, Mongolia.
 The ceremony of the delivery of the title was held in the building of the secretariat of the governor of Darhan Ol Province on Feb. 10. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 At the ceremony the chairman of the Presidium of the Conference of Citizens in Darhan Ol Province read a decision of the conference on awarding the title to Kim Jong Il and conveyed the certificate of the honorary citizen and medal to the DPRK ambassador to Mongolia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said in his speech that he regards it as great honor and pride to register Kim Jong Il as an honorary citizen of the province and award the certificate and medal to him on the occasion of his birthday, adding that he would make positive efforts for developing the friendly relations between Mongolia and the DPRK in the future, too.

Grand March for Peace Staged in S. Korea 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- A February 12 grand march for peace was staged in Phaengsong town of Phyongthaek City, Kyonggi Province on Feb. 12 as part of the actions against the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek and forcible expropriation of land and for peace on the Korean Peninsula. It was sponsored by the All-People Measure Committee for Checking the Expansion of the U.S. Military Base in Phyongthaek.
 Participating in it were members of civic and public organizations, inhabitants in the area designated as a site for the expanded U.S. military base in Phyongthaek, members of the Democratic Workers' Party and peace activists from different countries, at least 3,000 in all. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A meeting took place at the playground of the Taechu Primary School in Phaengsong town.
 A message declaring the start of the grand peace march was read out at the meeting. It demanded the "government" totally cancel the plan for expanding the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek according to the will of the people who love peace, though belatedly.
 The meeting was followed by the grand peace march. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, members of 12 religious organizations including the Hyangrin Church held a peace prayer service of Christians for checking the expansion of the U.S. military base in Phyongthaek on the same day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The organizations in a joint statement voiced their opposition to the expansion of the base aimed at threatening peace on the Korean Peninsula and depriving the Phaengsong inhabitants of their cradle. They vowed to fight against the government's forcible expropriation of land.

Demonstration Synchronized Swimming Presented 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- A demonstration synchronized swimming took place at the swimming pool of the Changgwang Health Complex Wednesday to celebrate February 16, the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 It was appreciated by Choe Yong Rim, Kim Jung Rin and other officials and working people in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present there on invitation were a congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan headed by Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, and other congratulatory groups of overseas compatriots, delegations and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The "Song Devoted to Comrade Kim Jong Il" resounded through the pool when it was pervaded with the high national pride and immense happiness of holding Kim Jong Il in high esteem as the great sun of the 21st century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The performers presented graceful rhythms of synchronized swimming and refined teamwork, reflecting the best wishes extended by the Korean people and the world's progressive humankind to Kim Jong Il on the occasion of the greatest national jubilee. 
 Through their numbers including "Thunder on Jong Il Peak", "Our General Is Best", "Ye, Bright Moon over My Country", "General and Children" they depicted with beautiful rhythms and refined skills the immortal feats  Kim Jong Il has performed by ushering in the era of a new leap forward in the building of a great prosperous powerful nation with his Songun revolutionary leadership and the unanimous desire of the servicepersons and people of the DPRK to revere the illustrious commander of Mt. Paektu and follow him to the last. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "For the Motherland," "This Is My Country" and other numbers won a high acclaim of the spectators as their performers successfully represented the ideological and thematic contents of the numbers with admirable synchronized swimming skills.
 The demonstration presentation ended with "Let's Advance Faster for Higher Goal" that reflected the firm faith and will of the servicepersons and people of the DPRK to effect a fresh surge in the building of a great prosperous powerful socialist nation.

Congratulatory Letter to Kim Jong Il from Chongryon 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory letter from the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongryon) on Feb. 16 on the occasion of his birthday.
ï¿½@The letter said the DPRK has firmly protected the dignity as a sovereign state, thereby defending the homeland despite rigorous ordeals and demonstrating its might as a powerful socialist state which has so unbreakable single-minded unity and capability to defend itself as firm as an iron-wall that no formidable enemy dares provoke it, adding that this is the brilliant fruition of the Songun idea, Songun leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter noted that celebrating the significant February holiday, all the officials of Chongryon and Koreans in Japan are filled with the firm resolution to surely achieve fresh growth and progress in the movement of Koreans in Japan as intended by 
Kim Jong Il, looking up toward the blue sky over the homeland where he is and sharing  the same will, intention and destiny with him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The letter evinced the determination to vigorously turn out in the patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and great national unity under the banner of "By our nation itself" and keep pace with the dynamic drive of the people in the homeland and thereby make a tangible contribution to the building of a socialist economic power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will widely introduce your greatness and strengthen friendship and international solidarity with the Japanese people to build a public opinion favorable for urging Japan to redress its unsavory past according to the DPRK-Japan Pyongyang Declaration and take a sincere approach toward the normalization of the relations between the DPRK and Japan, the letter said.

15th International Figure Skating Festival for "Paektusan Cup" Opens 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- The 15th International Figure Skating Festival for "Paektusan Cup" opened here on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il. 
 An opening ceremony took place at the Ice Rink on Feb. 15.
 Present there were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea (WPK), officials concerned and working people and sportspersons in the city. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also present were congratulatory groups of overseas Koreans including the congratulatory group of Koreans in Japan led by Nam Sung U, vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, delegations, diplomatic envoys of different countries and staff members of various embassies here and foreign guests. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of the song "Congratulations on February Holiday", players of the DPRK, China, Russia, Belarus, Slovakia, Ukraine, Uzbekistan, the Czech Republic and Kazakhstan entered the ice rink amid the warm welcome of the spectators.
 Mun Jae Dok, chairman of the Physical Culture and Sports Guidance Commission, in his opening address expressed belief that the festival that has opened amid the best wishes of the Korean people and progressive humankind for Kim Jong Il would make great success thanks to the sincere efforts of the Korean sportspersons and close friends from other countries. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The festival flag was hoisted while the song "The Brilliant Homeland" was solemnly played. 
 A group of Korean figure skaters gave a performance at the opening ceremony.
 They impressively represented the ardent reverence of the Korean people and the world progressive people for Kim Jong Il who has performed the great immortal exploits on behalf of the times and history and their high praise of the great man with admirable rhythms to the tune of the song "Old Home Clad in Snow Flakes".
 Through the numbers including "The Sound of a Horse's Hooves in Mt. Paektu", "Twelve Months for Songun Victory", "Blue Sky over My Country" and "For the Motherland" they successfully represented the firm spirit and will of the Korean army and people to make a higher leap forward full of great ambition and confidence under the Songun revolutionary leadership of the WPK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Then followed exhibition performances given by figure skaters from different countries including China, Kazakhstan and Slovakia. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They were highly acclaimed by the spectators each time they displayed high skating skills and refined and graceful movements.

Congratulatory Letter to Kim Jong Il from C.C., AINDF 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- Leader Kim Jong Il received a congratulatory letter from the Central Committee of the Anti-Imperialist National Democratic Front Thursday on the occasion of his birthday.
 Recalling that Kim Jong Il was born as a bright star over Mt. Paektu amidst the blessings of the era in the area where fierce battles were fought to win the great victory in the anti-Japanese revolution, the letter said that this was a great fortune for the nation as it promised a rosy future for carrying forward the revolutionary cause of Juche and a historic event which ushered in a new era of the human cause of independence. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was thanks to his birthday that the Korean nation has successfully carried out the cause of national independence century after century and dynamically steered the era of independence, exalting its dignity as the proud nation of holding the outstanding leader in high esteem down through generations, it said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is also thanks to the leadership of Kim Jong Il endowed with the noble sense of moral obligation, extraordinary leadership ability, iron will and matchless grit that there has begun in the north a new era of carrying out the cause of perpetuating the memory of President Kim Il Sung unprecedented in history and it has decisively shattered the unprecedented moves of the imperialist allied forces to isolate and stifle it to make a solemn gunfire for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, the letter noted, and continued: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Your personality as a great man and the undying leadership exploits you have performed by demonstrating the dignity of the nation to the whole world and victoriously leading socialism of Juche, the building of a great prosperous powerful nation, national reunification and the cause of independence against imperialism with the might of Songun convince the fellow countrymen in the south of a happy day of national reunification and a bright morrow of the nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will encourage the people from all walks of life to fully support and remain true to the patriotic Songun policy pursued you and turn out as one in the patriotic movement for independent reunification, peace against war and overall great unity under the uplifted banner of "By our nation itself". &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will wage a more dynamic struggle against the U.S. and war to deal a deadly blow at the U.S. colonial rule and decisively frustrate the attempt of the pro-U.S. conservative group to come to power again through a strong anti-conservative alliance and thus certainly open up a new phase of independent reunification.

Public Presentation of Experience in Cultivating Kimjongilia Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- A public presentation of the experience in cultivating Kimjongilia was held at the Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia Exhibition on Feb. 15.
 It brought together cultivators and researchers of Kimilsungia-Kimjongilia greenhouses of ministries and national institutions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Speakers presented the technique and experience they have gained in the course of cultivating Kimjongilia recognized as the world's most famous flower to be in more red and beautiful bloom. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They said that highly proud and honored to raise the flower loved by humankind for being a flower devoted to the great man, they have achieved shining successes in cultivating and propagating the flower by paying primary attention to proper manuring and cultivation and provision of good conditions for its growth suited to the natural and climatic conditions and cultivation conditions of greenhouses in Korea.

Reception Given by Cuban Ambassador
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- Cuban Ambassador to the DPRK Ruben Perez Valdes gave a reception on Feb. 15 on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Present there on invitation were Yang Hyong Sop, vice-president of the Presidium of the Supreme People's Assembly, Ro Tu Chol, vice-premier of the Cabinet, Kim Yong Jin, minister of Education, Ryom Sun Gil, chairman of the Central Committee of the General Federation of Trade Unions of Korea, Kim Kyong Ho, first secretary of the Central Committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League, Pak Sun Hui, chairperson of the Central Committee of the Korean Democratic Women's Union, and other officials concerned. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On hand were staff members of the Cuban embassy. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The ambassador in his speech highly praised the heroic struggle waged by the Korean people for the building of socialism and national reunification under the wise and tested leadership of Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The friendly relations between Cuba and the DPRK have grown stronger under the deep care of Kim Jong Il, the ambassador said, wishing him good health.
 Yang Hyong Sop, speaking next, said that Kim Jong Il has firmly defended the country, the revolution and socialism and laid a firm foundation for building a great prosperous powerful nation, while shattering the vicious moves of the hostile forces against the DPRK for the last more than decade under the uplifted banner of Songun.
 The fraternal relations of friendship and cooperation between the DPRK and Cuba provided by President Kim Il Sung and Comrade Fidel Castro Ruz have grown stronger day by day under the particular care of the top leaders of the two countries, he said, wishing the fraternal Cuban people greater success in their struggle to foil the U.S. imperialists' moves against socialism and defend the country, the revolution and the gains of socialism, rallied close around the Communist Party of Cuba headed by Fidel Castro Ruz.

Military Attaches Corps Feted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- The Ministry of the People's Armed Forces gave a reception on Feb. 15 for the military attaches corps here on the occasion of the birthday of leader Kim Jong Il.
 Present there on invitation were members of the corps. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Jong Gak, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, in his speech said that the birth of Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il was a historic event of the nation as it guaranteed the destiny, future, dignity and honor of Kim Il Sung's nation. As led by Kim Jong Il, the Korean revolution has always advanced along the road of victory despite all sorts of ordeals of history, he noted. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean People's Army will always creditably discharge the sacred mission and duty to devotedly defend the headquarters of the revolution by firmly trusting and following the supreme commander only and sharing the will, intention and destiny with him, the speaker said, and went on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 We will as ever continue developing the friendly and cooperative relations with the armies of various countries on the road of peace against imperialism under the banner of independence, peace and friendship. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Military attache of the Cuban embassy Giraldo Abreu Morales who is doyen of the corps referred to the fact that Kim Jong Il, born as the son of guerrillas in Mt. Paektu, a holy mountain of Korea, set out the idea of attaching importance to the army long ago and has strengthened the KPA into a strong army capable of defeating any formidable enemy.
 He hoped that the officers and men of the KPA and the Korean people would register greater success in the struggle to build a great prosperous powerful nation and reunify the country under the leadership of Kim Jong Il, true to the wish of eternal President Kim Il Sung. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants significantly celebrated the February holiday, singing songs and reciting poems praising Kim Jong Il.

Papers Editorially Celebrate February Holiday
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- Papers here today dedicate editorials to February 16, an auspicious holiday.
 Rodong Sinmun says that leader Kim Jong Il's history of revolutionary activities is the history of the great statesman and leader who has brought a bright prospect of the socialist cause in our era, weathering out the stern tempest of the revolution.
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the victory of Korean-style socialism built by President  Kim Il Sung has been successfully carried forward by Kim Jong Il. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is thanks to his leadership that the army and people of the DPRK have always been optimistic about the future of Korean-style socialism despite so rigorous trials. 
 He is a great guide who has indicated the road of the socialist cause in our era with his unique ideas and theories. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He laid a solid foundation for the building of a great prosperous powerful nation and put the dignity and position of the country and the nation on the highest level despite stern ordeals baffling human imagination. This is the undying feat performed by him.
 Underscoring the need to carry forward the ever-victorious history of the Korean revolution and accomplish the cause of Korean style socialism true to the Songun leadership of the great headquarters of the revolution, the paper calls on all the servicepersons and people to repose undisputed trust in Kim Jong Il and devotedly protect the headquarters of the revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  They should firmly trust and follow him only in any adversity with the iron faith and will that he represents their destiny and their country and socialism would be unthinkable without his leadership, it says, and continues:
 His Songun politics serves as a banner for winning the sure victory of Korean-style socialism. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is no other way for them than to apply the Songun political mode, regarding the Songun idea as guidelines. Songun means socialism and vice versa.
 It is necessary to intensify the drive to bring about a great Songun revolutionary surge in all fields of revolution and construction. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The banner of Juche, the banner of socialism, will always remain a banner of revolution which we should hold aloft. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson calls on all the servicepersons and people to hold Kim Jong Il in high esteem with pure conscience, maintaining the firm stand that they know Kim Jong Il only as he represents the brain of the Korean revolution and is a central figure for the unity.

Leader and Songun
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- The ever-victorious tradition of the Korean Revolution that was pioneered at the point of bayonet is being successfully carried forward under the guidance of Kim Jong Il, the brilliant commander of Songun.
 Born in Mt. Paektu on February 16, Juche 31 (1942) during the warfare against the Japanese imperialists, he grew up among guerrillas  and experienced the importance of guns more keenly than anybody else. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Seeing the military parade at the opening ceremony of Pyongyang Institute in February 1946 and the military parade of the Korean People's Army (KPA) in February 1948 after national liberation, he firmly resolved to strengthen the army into an invincible one so that no formidable enemy could invade Korea again.
 In order to guarantee the final victory of the Korean revolution by dint of arms, he gave field guidance to the Guard Seoul 105 Tank Division named after Ryu Kyong Su of the KPA on August 25, 1960, which marked the start of his Songun revolutionary leadership. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 From then on he has been putting his heart and soul into strengthening the KPA to be matchless revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu, inspecting one unit after another.
 He has successfully applied President Kim Il Sung's idea and line on attaching importance to the military affairs in his Songun politics to powerfully push forward with the socialist cause of Juche. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Over the last ten-odd years in particular, he has further cemented the military position and the single-minded unity of the revolutionary ranks with the KPA as the core and as the driving force and shattered the enemy's persistent moves to isolate and stifle the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The distance covered by him for the inspection tour of KPA units in the year of 1996 alone to defend the dignity and sovereignty of the country and the nation totaled over 10,000 kilometers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His inspection tour of Songun has served as a powerful driving force in increasing the combat capability of the KPA in every way and making the whole society replete with the revolutionary soldier spirit, inspiring the people and the army to build a great prosperous powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people, under the leadership of the brilliant commander of Mt. Paektu, will glorify the ever-victorious history, the history of Songun without the slightest vacillation in any trial and adversity.

Evening Gala of Servicepersons Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, February 16 (KCNA) -- An evening gala of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces took place at Jonsung Square on Feb. 15 to celebrate the auspicious February holiday. 
 Attending the gala were Minister Kim Il Chol and leading officials of the ministry and servicepersons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Amid the playing of "Congratulations on February Holiday", "February Is Spring" and other songs, the participants danced, extending the greatest glory and the warmest congratulations to Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il who was born as a great son of guerrillas and has led the revolutionary cause of Songun which started in the forest of Mt. Paektu. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 They also danced to the tune of such songs as "Worthwhile Military Service" and "Blue Sky over My Country", waving flags of the KPA Supreme Commander, the Workers' Party of Korea and the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Dancing to the tune of song "We Will Defend the Headquarters of Revolution with Our Lives", the participants renewed their iron will to remain loyal to the idea and leadership of Kim Jong Il and fully display the invincible might of the ranks of human bullets and bombs ready to devotedly defend their leader, the strong revolutionary army of Mt. Paektu, in the struggle to defend socialism and build a great prosperous powerful nation.
